## Task ID
BP-023a

## Context Loaded
@frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_defines_pkg.sv
@frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_structs_pkg.sv

## Hypothesis
Adding arbitration parameters and structs to the package files
is a self-contained change that can be verified by lint alone.
All 12 existing build targets must remain green.

## Background
bp_arb_spec.md (planning/arch/bp_arb_spec.md) defines a
credit-based PQ/UQ arbiter for each RAM-based predictor.
BP-023a adds the parameter and struct definitions required by
that spec. RTL changes to tage.sv and tage_cntrl.sv are
deferred to BP-023b.

## Binding Previous Decisions
- bp_defines_pkg.sv contains parameters only. No structs,
  no logic.
- bp_structs_pkg.sv contains structs, enums, typedefs only.
- Import order is mandatory everywhere:
    import bp_defines_pkg::*;
    import bp_structs_pkg::*;
- All field-width parameters carry predictor prefix:
  TAGE_MAX_*, SC_MAX_*, IT_MAX_*.
- Package files are at:
    frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_defines_pkg.sv
    frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_structs_pkg.sv

## Specific Requirements

### bp_defines_pkg.sv changes

1. Add TAGE arbitration parameters in a clearly marked section
   after the existing TAGE parameters. Use the exact values
   from bp_arb_spec.md section 4.2:

     localparam int TAGE_PQ_DEPTH       = 8;
     localparam int TAGE_UQ_DEPTH       = 8;
     localparam int TAGE_UQ_WR_PORTS    = 2;
     localparam int TAGE_RESP_BUF_DEPTH = 2;
     localparam int TAGE_PRED_CREDITS   = 4;
     localparam int TAGE_UPD_CREDITS    = 1;
     localparam int TAGE_STARVE_THRESH  = 8;

2. Add stub parameter sections for FTB, LP, SC, ITTAGE
   arbitration. All values are 0 with a comment // TBD.
   Use the same parameter names as TAGE with the appropriate
   prefix. SC has no UQ parameters (shares TAGE UQ) -- add
   only SC_RESP_BUF_DEPTH = 0 // TBD.

### bp_structs_pkg.sv changes

3. Add bp_arb_trx_t per spec section 4.6:

     typedef struct packed {
       logic                              trx_type;
       logic [$clog2(NUM_PRED_SLOTS)-1:0] trx_slot;
     } bp_arb_trx_t;

   trx_type encoding: 0 = PRED, 1 = UPD.

4. Add sc_pred_meta_t placeholder stub:

     // SC prediction metadata. Placeholder.
     // Fields to be defined when SC RTL is implemented.
     typedef struct packed {
       logic [7:0] reserved;
     } sc_pred_meta_t;

5. Add sc_upd_inp_t placeholder stub:

     // SC update input. Placeholder.
     // Fields to be defined when SC RTL is implemented.
     typedef struct packed {
       logic [7:0] reserved;
     } sc_upd_inp_t;

6. Add cond_pred_meta_t per spec section 6.1. This struct
   depends on tage_pred_meta_t (already defined) and
   sc_pred_meta_t (added above). Place after both
   dependencies:

     typedef struct packed {
       tage_pred_meta_t tage;
       sc_pred_meta_t   sc;
       logic            sc_valid;
     } cond_pred_meta_t;

7. Add cond_pred_upd_inp_t per spec section 6.1. This struct
   depends on tage_upd_inp_t (already defined) and
   sc_upd_inp_t (added above). Place after both
   dependencies:

     typedef struct packed {
       tage_upd_inp_t  tage;
       sc_upd_inp_t    sc;
       logic           sc_valid;
       logic           resolved_taken;
       logic           cond_mispredict;
     } cond_pred_upd_inp_t;

8. Verify bp_ras_snapshot_t is already defined in
   bp_structs_pkg.sv. If it is present, make no change to
   it and note its fields in Results Capture. If it is
   absent, stop and report before making any other change.

## Constraints
- Modify bp_defines_pkg.sv and bp_structs_pkg.sv only.
  No other file may be touched.
- No changes to any existing parameter, struct, or field.
  Additions only.
- sc_pred_meta_t and sc_upd_inp_t must be clearly marked
  as placeholders with comments as shown above.
- Struct declarations must appear after all their
  dependencies within bp_structs_pkg.sv.
- Line width 80 columns maximum.

## Deliverables
1. Updated frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_defines_pkg.sv.
2. Updated frontend/branch_predictor/rtl/bp_structs_pkg.sv.
3. Lint result: make lint (or equivalent covering both
   package files). Must exit zero with zero warnings under
   existing VER_FLAGS suppressions.
4. Confirm all 12 existing build targets still green.
5. Results Capture filled in below.
